License scope map — hapax-constitution

Copyright (c) Hapax Systems

This repository is dual-licensed BY PATH. It is not single-licensed as a
whole: no single license applies to the repository in its entirety. Each
path falls into exactly one of the two buckets below.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Specification and publication content — CC BY-NC-ND 4.0
   (full text: LICENSE-SPEC)

   - axioms/**
   - domains/**
   - knowledge/**
   - docs/**
   - research/**
   - demo/pipeline/domain_corpus/**
   - root-level *.md (README.md, NOTICE.md, GOVERNANCE.md,
     CONTRIBUTING.md, SECURITY.md, SUPPORT.md, and any other root
     markdown)
   - pattern-guide.md
   - operations-manual.md

2. Runnable tooling (the hapax-sdlc package) — Apache License 2.0
   (full text: LICENSE-APACHE)

   - sdlc/**
   - scripts/**
   - tests/**
   - demo/** except domain_corpus
   - .github/**
   - pyproject.toml
   - uv.lock
   - and all other code/config paths

--------------------------------------------------------------------------

Default rule: any path not matched above falls under Bucket 1 if it is
documentation or specification text, and under Bucket 2 if it is code or
configuration; when in doubt, treat it as Bucket 1 (the more restrictive
posture for reuse).

Prior distributions of this repository were made under the Apache License
2.0 in their entirety; that grant is irrevocable for the versions so
distributed. The split posture above applies from commit <SHA-PLACEHOLDER>
(2026-07-09) forward.

Note: GitHub license detection is expected to report NOASSERTION for this
layout; that is the intended result of a per-path split, not an error.
The machine-readable posture for this repository lives in hapax-council
docs/repo-pres/repo-registry.yaml (the expected_github_license_detection
pin).
